## Development Workflow

### Running Hugo Locally (Windows)
```powershell
# Start dev server with drafts visible
hugo server --buildDrafts --buildFuture

# Start with a specific port
hugo server --buildDrafts --buildFuture --port 1313

# Build the site without serving (check for errors)
hugo --gc --minify
```
The dev server runs at `http://localhost:1313/` with live reload.

### Running Hugo in Cloud/CI Environment (Linux)
```bash
# Install Hugo Extended (required for Congo theme SCSS)
wget -O /tmp/hugo.deb https://github.com/gohugoio/hugo/releases/download/v0.148.0/hugo_extended_0.148.0_linux-amd64.deb
sudo dpkg -i /tmp/hugo.deb

# Clone with submodules (required for Congo theme)
git clone --recurse-submodules https://github.com/ksopyla/ksopyla-ai-blog.git

# Build
hugo --gc --minify
```
Hugo Extended is required because the Congo theme uses SCSS.

