## Git and Deployment

### Commit and Push Workflow
1. Stage content changes: `git add content/ notes/`
2. Use conventional commit messages:
   - `content: add post on concept collapse` (new post)
   - `content: update draft for MoE explanation` (draft changes)
   - `content(linkedin): add research log #1` (social content)
   - `chore: update theme submodule` (infrastructure)
   - `fix: correct image paths in pytorch course post` (fixes)
3. Push to `main`: `git push origin main`

### GitHub Actions Auto-Deployment
On push to `main`, the workflow `.github/workflows/hugo-deployment.yml` automatically:
1. Installs Hugo Extended 0.148.0 + Dart Sass 1.89.2
2. Checks out repo with submodules
3. Builds with `hugo --gc --minify`
4. Deploys to GitHub Pages at https://ai.ksopyla.com/

The deploy takes ~1-2 minutes. Monitor at: https://github.com/ksopyla/ksopyla-ai-blog/actions

### Manual Deployment Trigger
If needed, trigger a deploy without pushing code:
- Go to https://github.com/ksopyla/ksopyla-ai-blog/actions
- Select "Deploy Hugo site to Pages" workflow
- Click "Run workflow"

### What Gets Deployed
Only content in `content/posts/` with `draft: false` is deployed. Content in `content/drafts/`, `content/linkedin/`, `content/x-threads/`, and `notes/` is NOT deployed (drafts are excluded by Hugo, social content folders have `_build: render: never`).


